<paragraph blockId="1.[151,610,405,467]" box="[151,263,441,467]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">
(
<figureCitation box="[160,254,441,467]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 1" captionStart-1="FIGURE 2" captionStartId-0="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,250,1346,1371]" captionTargetBox-0="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1435,452,1320]" captionTargetId-0="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId-1="figure@3.[151,1435,452,1320]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." captionText-1="FIGURE 2. Habitus lateral view of Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A. male; B. female." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702923" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3702923/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1–2</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,512,1973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,370,512,539]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Body small, medium size for the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1838" box="[799,964,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Meconematini">Meconematini</taxonomicName>
, robust. Fastigium verticis conical, stubby, apex obtusely rounded, with a thin median sulcus. Eyes oval, protruding forwards and outwards. Maxillary palpus slender, apical segment longer than subapical one, slightly swollen apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,512,1973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">
Pronotum short, posterior margin reaching middle area of first abdominal tergite, anterior margin faintly straight while posterior margin arc-shaped; disc smooth, only posterior transverse sulcus distinct (
<figureCitation box="[1150,1239,657,683]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); lateral lobe longer than deep, posterior margin tapering, without humeral sinus (
<figureCitation box="[878,965,693,719]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Thoracic auditory spiracle exposed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,512,1973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">
Tegmina somewhat short, apices not reaching posterior margin of pronotum, visible in lateral view in some specimens, while some slightly surpassing posterior margin of pronotum, visible in dorsal view; apices of tegmina obtusely rounded (
<figureCitation box="[360,449,801,827]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); hind wings absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,512,1973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">All femora unarmed ventrally, genicular lobes with apices obtuse. Fore coxae with 1 short spine; tibiae with 5–6 spines respectively on both sides of ventral surface, tibial tympana open on both sides, oval. Middle tibiae with 5 inner and 6 outer spines on ventral surface. Hind tibiae with 2 inner and 3 outer spines on ventral surface as well as 26–30 spines on both sides of dorsal surface, bearing 2 pairs of ventral apical spurs and 1 pair of dorsal apical spurs.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,512,1973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">
The length of first to eighth abdominal segments is shorter than half of abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[1133,1225,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1346,1371]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,452,1320]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,452,1320]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus lateral view of Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A. male; B. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702923/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Ninth abdominal tergite rather strikingly swollen, of which posterior margin concave (
<figureCitation box="[914,976,1053,1079]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
C–D). Tenth abdominal tergite obviously prolonged posteriorly, 1/3 basal area slightly broad while 2/3 apical area narrow, lateral margins almost parallel, with a deep longitudinal groove in the midline (
<figureCitation box="[678,739,1125,1151]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
D–E); ventral surface near middle area with a moundy process (
<figureCitation box="[160,251,1161,1187]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
); apex of tenth abdominal tergite blunt, gently expanded ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1115,1161,1187]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
), centre of posterior margin spilt. Cerci short, conical, apices subacute; inner surface of subapical areas with 1 spiniform process, of which terminal subacute (
<figureCitation box="[366,444,1233,1259]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
). Tenth abdominal sternite fused with subgenital plate (with trace of fusion), broad, flat in ventral view, rectangular, basal area concave (
<figureCitation box="[697,782,1269,1295]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1F</figureCitation>
); lateral surfaces of apical half folded dorsad and strongly expanded, triangular, apical area narrow, terminal obtusely rounded; styli absent (
<figureCitation box="[1060,1180,1305,1331]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1C, E</figureCitation>
). Genitalia sclerotized, not surpassing posterior margin of subgenital plate, apical area expanded, centre of dorsal margin conspicuously concave (
<figureCitation box="[258,347,1377,1403]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1G</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,512,1973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1413,1439]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Female.</emphasis>
Pronotum is similar to that of male; posterior margin of lateral lobe gradually narrowing; humeral sinus absent. Tegmina short, deposited laterally; some specimens exposed, visible in dorsal view; while tegmina of some specimens completely covered by pronotum. Appearance of first to seventh abdominal segments alike. Seventh abdominal sternite triangular, posterior margin bluntly rounded (
<figureCitation box="[975,1054,1521,1547]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1J</figureCitation>
). Eighth abdominal tergite faintly prolonged posteriorly, posterior margin arc-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[750,842,1557,1583]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1K</figureCitation>
); lateral margins strongly prolonged ventrally (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1L</figureCitation>
). Lateral margins of ninth abdominal tergite prolonged posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[945,1039,1593,1619]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1M</figureCitation>
); tenth abdominal tergite elongated posteriorly, basal area somewhat broad then tapering apically, with a U-shaped concavity in the middle on posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[244,332,1665,1691]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1K</figureCitation>
). Cerci conical, apices acute. Subgenital plate short and broad, slightly concave on posterior margin (
<figureCitation box="[160,245,1701,1727]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1L</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor stout, mildly bent dorsad, with tip subacute; dorsal and ventral margins smooth (
<figureCitation box="[1294,1387,1701,1727]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1M</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,512,1973]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1736,1763]" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Coloration.</emphasis>
Body green when alive, while yellowish green when dried and pinned (
<figureCitation box="[1151,1218,1737,1763]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1346,1371]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,452,1320]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,452,1320]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Habitus lateral view of Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A. male; B. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702923/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A–B). Eyes brown. Fastigium verticis brown. Dorsal area of head with 1 longitudinal light brown stripe in the midline. Disc of pronotum with 1 broad longitudinal light brown stripe, 3/4 anterior area of which with a black brown edge on each lateral margin, outer margins with 1 longitudinal light yellow stripe respectively (
<figureCitation box="[974,1062,1845,1871]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Dorsal surface of abdomen with 1 longitudinal light brown stripe. Basal area of tenth abdominal tergite with a black brown spot in the middle (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1D, K</figureCitation>
). Inner spiniform process of male cercus black brown (
<figureCitation box="[836,912,1910,1936]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1829,1854]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1801]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Paradoxitettigia longicaudica sp. nov.: A–B. pronotum: A. dorsal view; B. lateral view; C–E, H, K, M. apex of abdomen: C, M. lateral view; D, K. dorsal view; E. apical view; H. antero-lateral view; F, L. subgenital plate in ventral view; G. genitalia in apical view; I. right cercus in latero-dorsal view; J. seventh –eighthabdominal sternites in anterior view. A–I. male; J–M. female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3702921" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3702921/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="139">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
). Apices of all third segment of tarsi and claws brown, apices of dorsal spines on hind tibiae brown.
</paragraph>
